<TEXT>
a small town library was set free from 
budget woes when officials found an original copy of abraham 
lincolns emancipation proclamation lying in a pile of junk 
it was like a providential finding said maurice isserman a 
trustee of the ashfield public library and a professor of history 
at mount holyoke college in south hadley 
isserman discovered the document last fall as trustees were 
meeting to discuss the prospect of receiving state and federal 
grants 
somebody said we could sell those old prints over there in the 
corner isserman said i walked over and looked at one and it 
wasnt a print it was a document and i looked down at the bottom 
and there was abraham lincolns signature which was faded a 
different color from the printed material 
the document was one of 48 copies made in 1864 and signed by 
lincoln and secretary of state william seward experts at sothebys 
auction house in new york told trustees recently 
library officials believe the document was donated years ago by 
george william curtis a friend of lincolns and a founder of the 
ashfield library association 
the library received its grants but they totaled about 50000 
less than officials expected the threeroom belding memorial 
library also needed renovations isserman said 
so the document will be auctioned next fall and is expected to 
fetch at least 70000 which should cover the renovations he said 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
a texas businessman has just the thing 
for the jet lagged rhinoceros an airport vip lounge for animals 
thomas c schooler is preparing to build the lounge at 
dallasfort worth international airport his first arrivals a 
party of 10 rare black rhinos are scheduled to stop here june 16 
the hulking visitors will be treated to a shower and sprayed for 
harmful parasites before dining on a vegetarian meal its like a 
big car wash schooler said of the shower 
schooler has operated a similar rest stop in houston for three 
years he also has helped an entire rodeo make a worldwide tour and 
recently shipped a circus 
although construction wont start until next month schooler 
already is doing business in dallasfort worth 
i bring truckloads of animals up here to make connections with 
japan airlines or american he said last night 2000 chickens 
came in and are going out this morning 
the animalport which will occupy up to three acres at the 
airport also will cater to domesticated animals including cats 
dogs and horses 
harry tennison president of fort worthbased game conservation 
international which is importing the rhinos for zoos in dallas 
fort worth san diego and milwaukee said the animalport is needed 
it will be a great aid to our zoological people all over this 
part of the world he said 
