<TEXT>
agonizing personal experience led linda noie to 
her fervent antiabortion stance ten years ago she had an 
abortion but still carried a fetus to term and gave birth she 
shared her private anguish over that failed abortion with the 
associated press in a story that is one in a series examining the 
emotional question of abortion rights as the us supreme court 
prepares to hear arguments this week 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
two months after her abortion linda noie 
feared a cancerous tumor was growing inside her but the rhythmic 
buhbump of a fetal heartbeat heard through a stethoscope confirmed 
she was still pregnant 
my tumor had a heartbeat two beautiful arms and two beautiful 
legs ms noie said 
the episode in 1979 transformed ms noie into a zealous 
prolifer now the state director of women exploited by abortion 
she lives next door to the clinic where she had the fiveminute 
surgery and pickets there at least twice a week 
her son joshua now 9 years old joins her at marches rallies 
and speeches he wears a tshirt saying i survived the abortion 
holocaust 
if that baby could make it through that terrible experience 
that baby was mine no matter what ms noie 44 said nobody 
was going to talk me into killing this baby i thought i committed 
murder one time i wasnt going to do it again 
there is a reason joshua survived i think god wanted to start 
his army in the spiritual battle against abortion he wanted 
somebody to be on the front lines here we are out on the 
battlefront 
nationally the bitter abortion fight is approaching a turning 
point 
the us supreme court will hear arguments april 26 on a 
missouri case that could narrow or overturn a 1973 ruling that 
established a womans right to abortion 
when defenders of a womans right to choose a safe legal 
abortion have marched on washington dc most recently april 9 
some have carried coat hangers as brutal reminders of backalley 
butchery done before 1973 
those opposed to abortion like ms noie counter with pictures of 
fetuses being cut up or sucked out of the womb she has yelled at 
patients and jumped in front of cars bringing pregnant women to the 
fox valley reproductive health care center where she had her 
unsuccessful abortion 
her mailbox is painted crimson and adorned with red ribbon to 
symbolize babies blood 
i dont want anyone else to get hurt like i was ms noie 
said i made a bad mistake it eats away at me every day i want 
to be there for somebody else i dont want them to look out and 
not have anybody like i did 
abortion doesnt just mean being unpregnant its legalized 
murder babies are being killed she said you just cant put 
it in a closet that door doesnt quite shut tight its going to 
creep out some day 
ms noie says shes on a crusade to help women who feel guilt or 
suffer psychological scars after their abortions dr vincent rue 
a psychotherapist and former teacher at ucla called this condition 
postabortion syndrome and said it can include suppressed 
hostility unresolved mourning for the loss of the fetal child and 
a reexperiencing of the abortion 
the way ms noie sees it the clinic either botched the abortion 
or aborted a twin fetus 
maggi case director and owner of the clinic declined to 
comment on ms noies case because she is not at liberty to 
discuss a patients medical records 
ms noie cried several times as she recounted her achingly 
private pain in a recent interview her gaze frequently drifted out 
the dining room window to a childs swing set and sandbox in the 
backyard 
in 1979 she was recently divorced after 15 years of marriage 
and had two children aged 16 and 10 a waitress she became 
pregnant to a restaurant customer who befriended her 
afraid confused and burdened with a pregnancy her boyfriend 
didnt want she scheduled an abortion at the clinic for jan 12 
the day of the surgery she wrote one word in her calendar 
diary slaughterhouse after a fivehour wait in the crowded 
clinic she spent five minutes on the operating table her 
boyfriend paid in cash 
i was mixed up i was wishing somebody would break in and take 
me out of there i wanted it stopped ms noie said the pain 
was awful it seemed very very wrong 
i killed a baby i felt so dirty and crummy it was like part 
of me was gone she said i couldnt look at myself in the 
mirror i was ready to commit suicide not because i wanted to die 
but because i hated myself so badly for what i had done 
that night she and her boyfriend ended their relationship 
ms noie returned a month later for a checkup complaining about 
being dizzy and weak at work she was told the abortion had 
removed particles of conception but her hormones hadnt 
readjusted 
on march 29 she came back again and was referred to a second 
doctor when he checked her for a suspected tumor she was given a 
stethoscope and was asked do you want to hear your babys 
heartbeat 
ms noie says her son has hearing lapses memory loss and other 
health effects that she attributes to the abortion 
she returned to the clinic about a year after joshua was born 
dressed in black she circled the stone and frame building 
touching it while joshua played with driveway pebbles 
i wanted to make sure it couldnt hurt me anymore she said 
a chainlink fence erected by the clinic marks the property line 
i had nightmares when i first moved in ms noie said i 
dreamed of little babies with charred arms and legs crawling out of 
the barrels in back where they burn their medical waste 
joshua likes the house but he tells people he lives next to 
the place where they kill babies she said once when he was 3 
years old he woke up screaming at night and said mommy why did 
you do it didnt you want me 
</TEXT>
