caretaker in the summer that tiny settlement swells to dozens who 
camp out for three months fishing 
heyano like nearly everyone around bristol bay following the 
prince william sound oil spill is adamantly opposed to oil and gas 
development in the precious fishing grounds 
the whole rhythm of our lives is based on fishing and 
subsistence hunting said heyano 37 if you werent able to do 
that i dont see how anyone could continue to live in a village 
