<TEXT>
the gender of a familys children once was 
determined by nature alone but modern prenatal testing techniques 
now enable expectant parents to make calculated decisions about 
having sons or daughters 
the tests in effect give parents an option although one that 
is rarely exercised pregnant with a girl but want a boy get an 
abortion and try again eventually you should get the gender of 
your choice 
many people consider this practice repugnant and perhaps a first 
step toward eugenics it is almost universally condemned by 
geneticists who conduct the prenatal tests those in favor of a 
womans right to abortion usually are opposed to gender choice and 
surveys show that only a very very few pregnant women will 
actually abort for sex selection 
but the fact that this type of family planning is possible and 
available is one of the dark undercurrents that continues to haunt 
the increasingly sophisticated world of modern human reproduction 
and it is an element cited by groups who oppose abortions made 
legal by the roe vs wade decision of the supreme court 
the court in a case from missouri is being asked to overturn 
or substantially limit that landmark 1973 decision arguments are 
scheduled wednesday in that case which does not specifically 
involve the genderselection issue 
the two types of prenatal testing chorion villus sampling and 
amniocentesis are used most frequently to determine if the fetus 
has some sort of genetic abnormality women who take these tests do 
so in anticipation of having an abortion if the fetus is shown to 
have a severe birth defect 
except for some rare genetic defects determining the gender is 
just an incidental part of the prenatal test findings but for some 
american couples apparently a rare few it is the whole point of 
the tests 
dr mark i evans a detroit doctor who is on the ethics 
committee of the american college of obstetrics and gynecology 
said the number of american women who use prenatal testing to 
control the gender of their children is incredibly minuscule 
in five years ive only been aware of two cases said 
evans who has a large practice specializing in prenatal testing 
thats two cases out of about 10000 its an incredibly 
minuscule problem and everybody is making a mountain out of a 
molehill 
evans however was concerned enough about the issue to take a 
survey of colleagues he found that 20 percent of the 212 doctors 
surveyed around the country believe gender selection is morally 
acceptable but nonetheless very few will actually participate in 
the practice and most said they very rarely are presented with the 
dilemma 
having talked to colleagues around the country ive found 
that everybodys experience is roughly the same said evans 
doctors who perform prenatal testing in philadelphia 
washington houston san francisco and other major centers all 
reported that they get so few requests for gender selection testing 
that it is not considered a problem of significance 
weve done 25000 prenatal diagnosis and it has happened to us 
only a few times said dr mitchell s goldbus of the university 
of california medical center in san francisco we run into it 
about one per thousand 
the policy at most centers is to specifically reject patients 
who ask for prenatal testing to determine gender alone but doctors 
admit they dont always know patients sometimes will request the 
testing for a genetic reason but actually are seeking the gender 
its possible to be fooled occasionally but i really think 
that on a percentage basis it is a very low number said evans 
one doctor who will perform prenatal testing for gender 
selection is dr gabriel khodr of san antonio and he reacts to 
criticism from other doctors in no uncertain terms 
who are they to impose their morality to others khodr asked 
in a telephone interview 
he said doctors will perform abortions for economic reasons for 
reasons of birth control or because the pregnancy is 
inconvenient for the mother but then balk at abortions for 
gender selection 
if they dont do abortions at all then i accept their 
point said khodr but if they do abortions then they dont 
have right to say i do abortions for any reason but sex 
selection why is it worse to want an abortion for family planning 
when youve got three girls and dont want another 
he adds i dont like abortions and i dont do abortions but 
who am i to force my morality on others 
khodr said that even though it is known that he will do prenatal 
testing for gender selection he still sees such patients only 
rarely 
he said last year he had two pregnant patients who requested the 
service for the same reason they both had three sons and were 
determined to have a daughter khodr said that by coincidence both 
women got their wish they gave birth to daughters 
evans and others however believe that prenatal testing should 
be used only to detect a possible disease or genetic defect 
permitting parents to select the gender of their offspring could 
eventually lead to a distortion of the natural balance of the 
sexes they feel since most parents asking for the service are 
usually seeking sons 
i am perfectly comfortable with pregnancy termination for 
genetic abnormalities but being female is not an abnormality 
said evans i am in favor of genetic testing i am not in favor 
of eugenics 
most of the genetic testing centers said requests for gender 
selection usually come from couples who are indian chinese or 
arab 
most of the family that use sex selection come from a culture 
that considers a male in the family to be important for social and 
economic stability said karen copeland a counselor at the 
baylor college of medicine genetics center in houston those are 
primarily chinese east indian and some of the middle eastern 
countries those are the ones who if they have several females will 
consider ending the pregnancy if its another girl 
ms copeland said she will turn such patients away from baylor 
but if asked will refer them to dr khodr 
</TEXT>
