the supreme court today set aside 720000 in 
awards won by the families of five uraguayans who were among the 
154 people killed in a 1982 airline crash in kenner la 
the justices ordered a federal appeals court to restudy the case 
in light of their decision last week that international airline 
passengers do not have to be warned about the 75000perperson 
liability cap for death or injury 
pan american world airways flight 759 crashed outside of new 
orleans shortly after its takeoff from moisant international 
airport on july 9 1982 investigators concluded that a wind shear 
contributed to the accident 
more than 50 of the crash victims were foreign tourists 
pan am never has contested its liability for the accident and 
the numerous lawsuits stemming from the crash have been limited to 
the question of what damages should be paid 
the two families of the five uraguayans luis and electra 
trivellonilorenzi sara lopez de pampin amparo pampin lopez and 
irma lopez de alvarez were awarded a total of 720000 by a 
federal jury in new orleans 
the trial was held only after pan ams request that it be 
allowed to defend against the two suits in uraguay was denied 
us district judge adrian g duplantier noted that the federal 
government likely would become a defendant after administrative 
maneuvers were completed and that the government could not be 
forced to defend itself in uraguayan courts 
he also ruled that pan am could not invoke the warsaw 
convention a treaty covering international airplane travel to 
limit its liability to 75000 for each death 
duplantier said pan am could not benefit from the treaty because 
the limited liability was discussed on passenger tickets in too 
small a size of print 9point rather than 10point 
his ruling was upheld by the full 5th us circuit court of 
appeals last july 21 
on april 18 the supreme court ruled in a similar case stemming 
from the soviet downing of a korean air lines jet that claimed 269 
lives in 1983 
the justices ruled that kal cannot be penalized for its failure 
to use the proper size type on its tickets to alert passengers to 
the 75000 limit 
the kal tickets used 8point type even smaller than that used 
on the pan am tickets in the case acted on today 
the case is pan am vs lopez 87750 
