no 2 gun turret he said fate has written a sorrowful chapter 
in the history of this great ship 
they came from hidalgo texas cleveland ohio tampa fla 
costa mesa california the president said they came to the 
navy as strangers served the navy as shipmates and friends and 
left the navy as brothers in eternity 
to the navy community remember that you have the admiration 
of america for sharing the burden of grief as a family bush said 
you must be heroically strong now to all who mourn a son 
a brother a husband a father a friend i can only offer you the 
gratitude of a nation for your loved one served his country with 
distinction and honor he said 
he said to the children of the lost crewmen you must never 
forget that your father was americas pride 
capt fred p moosally commander of the iowa said the men who 
died made the ultimate sacrifice for us the men of turret two 
will be part of the spirit of the iowa forever 
we shared the good the bad the comedy and now the tragedy 
moosally said 
after the service the president and his wife barbara moved 
through the crowd as the navy hymn played offering words of 
consolation shaking hands and hugging mourners many of them in 
tears the victims families then met with the ships commander 
privately 
on sunday night about 3000 family members and friends greeted 
the ship on its arrival at norfolk naval base exchanging tearful 
embraces with loved ones 
when the 887foot warship moved into sight of the dock families 
let out scattered cheers but as tugs pushed the ship into its 
berth the crowd fell silent all that could be heard were the 
cries of gulls that circled the iowas wake 
the barrels of the threegun turret were in the same position as 
when the explosion occurred off puerto rico on wednesday 
reporters were not allowed to talk with the families or the 
crewmen 
fiftyeight crewmen were in the turret when it exploded during 
gun exercises eleven sailors in the lowest level of the turret 
six decks below the guns survived 
the navy has refused to speculate on the cause of the explosion 
which damaged only the inside of the turret 
but navy teams said it appeared that the blast occurred while 
the powder bags were being loaded into the big gun the new york 
times reported sunday 
the navy on sunday released a videotape made by an officer on 
the bridge who wanted to record the firing of the guns 
the explosion appears to blast away the gasketlike rubber that 
seals the gun slits and is followed by a jet of fire and thick 
smoke from the gunhouse 
