1985 had offered his resignation and that hussein accepted it 
the four days of riots in which at least eight people died 
began tuesday in the southern city of maan and spread to dozens of 
cities and villages throughout the kingdom 
the official jordan news agency reported sunday that hussein had 
expressed his intention to deal with the roots of the problem and 
all the reasons and causes of the latest incidents within a short 
period of time 
many rioters chanted slogans calling for rifais ouster they 
also shouted their support for the king 
rifai has been widely blamed for falling living standards in 
jordan the annual per capita income has slumped from about 2000 
in the mid1980s to about 1200 
the government last year imposed import controls and austerity 
measures to help deal with mounting payments on a 6 billion debt 
the rioting was triggered by 10 percent to 50 percent increases 
in the prices of gasoline cigarettes and other commodities the 
price increases were carried out under an agreement with the 
international monetary fund to pave the way for rescheduling the 
debt payments 
rifai 52 was a boyhood friend of king hussein who became one 
of his most trusted advisers 
