<TEXT>
the number of violent crimes rose 5 percent 
last year the fbi said monday with aggravated assaults up 7 
percent 
the fbis preliminary uniform crime report for 1988 showed 
overall that reported crimes rose 3 percent from 1987 to 1988 
murders increased 3 percent and robberies were up 4 percent from 
1987 according to the statistics released sunday rapes went up 1 
percent and motor vehicle thefts increased 11 percent 
despite the general rise in killings the number of murders 
declined in three of the nations largest cities 
homicides reported to police dropped 88 percent in los angeles 
44 percent in chicago and 83 percent in detroit 
murders rose 64 percent in washington where authorities are 
blaming the dramatic increase in killings on warring drug dealers 
the bush administration has detailed extra fbi and drug 
enforcement administration agents to the nations capital to help 
local police fight the drugspawned crime wave 
murders increased 36 percent in houston 278 percent in 
indianapolis 27 percent in jacksonville fla 216 percent in 
