monday for the state income tax exempting all pensioners making 
less than 16000 a year but imposing taxes for the first time on 
state goverment retirees making more 
a us supreme court decision last month in a michigan case 
barred states from treating federal pensioners differently from 
retirees of state and local government agencies prompting baliles 
to call a special legislative session to amend virginias laws 
it is an unprecedented circumstance that has obliged me to 
call you back into special session the firstterm democratic 
governor told the general assembly the legislature has until 
thursday the end of the special session to take action 
virginia is one of 24 states that is affected by the march 28 
supreme court ruling because they impose income taxes on federal 
retirement pensions while exempting pensions paid to retired state 
and local public employees with nearly 200000 federal civilian 
and military retirees virginia is potentially hardest hit of all 
states 
in all baliles proposal would cost the state treasury about 
46 million the governor said the loss could be covered by reserve 
funds without cutting existing state programs 
the supreme court didnt spell out how states much tax their 
federal and state government pensioners only that the two groups 
must be treated equally 
baliles said he considered a number of options but chose the 
16000 cutoff because he believed it to be the most fair to 
retirees and state taxpayers 
he said his desire for fairness also prompted him to propose 
exempting retirees of private employers from the income tax if 
they make less than 16000 the high court decision did not cover 
private pensioners 
recognize this one fact whatever tax relief we give to one 
group of taxpayers in this case retirees will be at the expense 
of other virginia citizens baliles said that is unavoidable 
the supreme court said treat all public retirees the same 
he said i believe this plan does that and at the same time 
reaches out to grant private retirees identical tax relief 
baliles acknowledged his plan would not be liked by government 
retirees with higher incomes such as highranking military 
officers but if the plan had been in effect in 1987 baliles said 
four out of five retirees who filed a tax return would not have 
paid state income taxes 
social security benefits would be taxfree the governor said 
the pension tax would apply to people age 55 and over 
