<TEXT>
when noboru takeshita arrived at the pinnacle of 
japanese politics in november 1987 he was known as the best 
moneyraiser the liberal democratic party had ever known now he 
has been taken down by his field of expertise 
takeshita buffeted by a scandal over political donations that 
sent his opinionpoll ratings to rock bottom decided tuesday to 
resign as prime minister chief cabinet secretary keizo obuchi said 
in an announcement on live national television 
the decision came after takeshita was forced to acknowledge that 
he had received even more money than he had previously admitted 
from recruit co the conglomerate at the center of a 
moneypolitics scandal that has brought the resignations of three 
of his cabinet ministers and the arrests of 14 people on charges of 
bribery and securities law violations 
takeshita 65 had admitted to parliament that he received more 
than 1 million in what he called legal donations from recruit 
then news reports over the weekend said he also had borrowed 
381000 from recruit in 1987 takeshita on sunday said the report 
was true 
at the time of the loan takeshita was finance minister and 
campaigning to succeed yasuhiro nakasone as president of the 
governing liberal democrats and prime minister 
takeshita was regarded as a quiet political operator in 
contrast to nakasones flamboyant internationalism his strengths 
have been in patience administration and backroom politics 
consensusbuilding japanese style 
some doubted his underthetable political methods would serve 
japan well in an international context but he defeated his rivals 
in a campaign that left him with a reputation as the best 
fundraiser the conservative party had 
he embarked on a continuation of nakasones policy of opening 
japan to outside influences and imported goods plus an expansion 
of the domestic economy to reverse the countrys dependence on 
exports 
under his administration japan announced a vast expansion in aid 
to underdeveloped countries surpassing the united states as an aid 
donor tokyo won an improved reputation as a responsible and 
concerned member of the international community 
but last summer takeshita came under increasing fire as the 
recruit scandal unfolded with revelations that he and other 
politicians as well as bureaucrats and business and media leaders 
had profited from transactions in recruit shares 
takeshitas name however was not on the transactions which 
were done in the names of an aide and a relative the profit on the 
12000share transactions was estimated at a total of 192000 
the conglomerate allegedly seeking favors and influence had 
offered bargainpriced shares in a real estate subsidiary to the 
public figures who profited handsomely by selling after the 
subsidiarys shares went on public sale in late 1986 and the price 
skyrocketed 
in recent years the device of such sales became a way for 
companies to give money to politicians in excess of legal limits 
another way was to buy tickets to politicians fundraising 
parties and recruit was a major donor to takeshitas affairs 
with all the revelations takeshita was forced back to a posture 
of political reform and he said repeatedly he knew that politics 
had to change and he would lead the liberal democrats through the 
painful process 
in the end it wasnt enough and he was forced to step aside so 
that the party could head into this summers elections for half the 
upper house of parliament and general elections next year with a 
leadership untainted by recruit money 
takeshita was born feb 26 1924 as the eldest son of an old 
sake brewing family in shimane prefecture in western japan after 
service as a pilot trainee toward the end of world war ii he 
finished his university studies and taught english and social 
studies for several years before turning to politics 
he was elected to the shimane prefectural assembly at age 27 
and then won a seat in the powerful lower house of parliament in 
1958 when he was 34 
his political skills advanced him in a succession of key offices 
including chief cabinet secretary and construction minister he 
became finance minister in 1979 under prime minister masayoshi 
ohira continuing to hold that high post under nakasones 
administration 
