editors note if its pleasing to the nose theres probably a 
market for it thats the philosophy of aroma researchers at a new 
jersey company whose customers range from soap manufacturers to the 
makers of fine perfumes they even formulated a dinosaur 
vegetation fragrance for the philadelphia zoo 
