<TEXT>
f hoffmannla roche amp co the swiss 
chemical and pharmaceutical company today announced a major 
overhaul that involves formation of a holding company and 
elimination of its current share structure 
the restructuring is intended to increase management efficiency 
enhance operational flexibility and satisfy the markets call for a 
simpler share structure hoffmannla roche said the changes also 
take into account proposed reforms of the swiss company law 
the plan announced at a news conference in basel at which the 
company also released its latest financial results quieted 
speculation that hoffmannla roche would use the occasion to 
announce plans to seek control of another pharmaceutical concern 
hoffmannla roche chairman fritz gerber declined to comment on 
whether the new structure would place the company in a better 
position to launch a takeover bid for philidelphiabased smithkline 
beckman corp or britains beecham group plc the two companies 
have announced their intention to merge 
hoffmannla roches announcement last friday that it had 
scheduled a news conference for today to discuss a series of 
significant measures stirred speculation that it might be preparing 
an offer for one of the companies 
under the current twin share structure each owner of 
hoffmannla roche shares or dividend rights certificates also owns 
shares in sapac corp a new brunswick njbased affiliated 
company which handles business in north and south america asia 
parts of afria australia britain and other places 
the new structure would convert these dual stock holdings into 
shares in a holding company that would comprise interests held by 
both hoffmannla roche and sapac 
sapac shares are to be called in and sapac is to become a 
subsidiary of the new holding company called roche holding ag 
in addition the proposed group holding company would own a new 
baselbased subsidiary consisting of roche and sapacs operating 
functions 
a third stage of the restructuring would reshuffle and 
significantly enlarge hoffmannla roches stock base under the 
proposed structure the companys share capital would be increased 
in a series of stages 
gerber in describing the overhaul to reporters called it a 
logical step in the companys adjustment to future needs he said 
the changes would make hoffmannla roche stock more accessible to a 
broader base of investors 
separately hoffmannla roche said its profit rose 331 percent 
to 6415 million swiss francs the equivalent of 389 million at 
todays exchange rates up from from 482 francs in 1987 
